d made Ara promise to stay and watch over Themiscrya and those who remained.   Arahuta made the promise, and knew it meant she may have to break one she had made to herself.  That was to never kill.   She looked over the city of amazons and sighed.  And turned and walked to the smithy's barn.  There Hippolyte told her to chose any weapons.  Something that she would feel comfortable with and ready.  There were still warriors left in the city.  And they would stand with Ara in case of attack.  <br>
